	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> August 57</date>.</p>
				<p>The <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I am on here for a few days&#44; and<lb/> having got through a little business sooner than I expected<lb/> I <sic>purpose</sic> paying my <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> friends a short visit.<lb/>  I have written the enclosed to inform <persName>Mrs E. P. Cohen</persName> of my<lb/> intention&#8212;she having been polite enough to invite me to stay<lb/> at her house whenever I went to your city.  May I trouble<lb/> you to hand or send it to her at your earliest convenience<lb/> as I do not know her address.  If I am able to leave&#8212;and<lb/> I am yet not quite positive&#8212;it will be not later than <date>Friday</date> morng<lb/> If you wish to write me&#44; address to <persName>Rev. Lyons</persName>.  Hoping to have the pleasure<lb/> of seeing you soon&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
		</body>
	</text>
